Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.90,0:00:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Soccer was my reason for living.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.03,0:00:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I always dreamed of becoming\Na professional soccer player.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.45,0:00:19.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought that happiness came from fame,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.13,0:00:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,a good career,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.92,0:00:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,money.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.97,0:00:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was six,\Nmy parents signed me up for soccer.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.18,0:00:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I really loved playing soccer.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.89,0:00:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I spent all my time at the stadium,\Neven late into the night.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.10,0:00:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was 12,\NI learned about Jehovah from my mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.19,0:00:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,At that time,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.82,0:00:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,she started studying the Bible.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.28,0:00:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And after about a year,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.32,0:00:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I began to preach from door to door.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.74,0:00:55.16,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was 17 years old,\NI finished school
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.16,0:00:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and I received an invitation\Nfrom the Dynamo Soccer Club in Kiev.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.75,0:01:03.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that was unforgettable!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.25,0:01:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, my emotions were running high
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.21,0:01:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,because since childhood\NI had always dreamed of playing for Dynamo.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.22,0:01:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,From that moment on,\Nall my energy and all my time
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.93,0:01:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,were devoted to my career.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.69,0:01:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Every day we either trained or there was a game.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.16,0:01:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,There was no time left for spiritual things.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.62,0:01:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, being around people like that,\NI became just like them.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.17,0:01:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I led an immoral lifestyle
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.09,0:01:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,because huge amounts of money\Nopened up many opportunities.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.35,0:02:02.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Going to nightclubs, the nightlife
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.52,0:02:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,—it was so immoral.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.06,0:02:09.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone wants to be\Nyour friend and to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.02,0:02:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, this was tempting.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.74,0:02:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I also invested huge sums\Nof money in real estate.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.96,0:02:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to create a foundation\Nfor the future and wealth for myself,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.67,0:02:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,my family, and my relatives\Nso that no one would be in need.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.84,0:02:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I was sure that this really was happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.84,0:02:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,This continued for nine years.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.81,0:02:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The turning point
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.85,0:02:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,was a conversation with management\Nwhen an issue came up,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.48,0:02:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and they hurled insults at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.44,0:02:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,At that moment, I felt worthless,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.44,0:02:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,like a disposable cup
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.86,0:02:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,that you use and then crush
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.61,0:02:59.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and throw away.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.41,0:03:03.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, a new generation\Nof soccer players was arriving
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.66,0:03:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,—many young guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.00,0:03:08.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I stopped being included in the starting lineup.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.25,0:03:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, the financial crisis began,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.71,0:03:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and real estate prices fell drastically.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.88,0:03:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I panicked; I didn’t know what to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.80,0:03:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And I started to think about the meaning of life:
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.85,0:03:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,‘What really is the meaning of life?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.27,0:03:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,‘If it’s not a career, not money
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.60,0:03:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,—then what is it?’
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.52,0:03:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I remembered everything that I learned
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.90,0:03:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,about Jehovah when I was a teenager.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.03,0:03:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I began to study\Nthe Bible again along with my wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.24,0:03:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,After a year, I started preaching again,\Nand in 2009,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.24,0:03:46.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I was baptized as one of Jehovah’s Witnesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.75,0:03:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And this brought me so much joy and satisfaction.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.88,0:03:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,These feelings can’t be compared\Nto winning any medal or cup.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.47,0:04:02.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I realized that I couldn’t slave for two masters,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.72,0:04:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,but I still had to play\Ntwo more years for Dynamo Kyiv.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.77,0:04:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Although it was a difficult time,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.11,0:04:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I took advantage of this opportunity,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.36,0:04:16.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and I am thankful to Jehovah that a good witness
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.19,0:04:18.53,Default,,0,0,0,,was given about his name.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.53,0:04:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,There were some soccer players
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.45,0:04:23.45,Default,,0,0,0,,who showed interest in the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.45,0:04:27.79,Default,,0,0,0,,In 2011 when my contract ended,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.79,0:04:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I finished my professional career.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.54,0:04:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,First Timothy chapter 6
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.54,0:04:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,encourages us “to place [our] hope,\Nnot on uncertain riches,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.92,0:04:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,but on God,” and “to be rich in fine works.”
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.26,0:04:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,People ask me: “Do you regret it?”
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.01,0:04:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,“Maybe you’d like to come back;\Ndo you miss soccer?”
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.48,0:04:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And I honestly and sincerely say no.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.85,0:04:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t miss it, and I don’t want to go back
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.36,0:04:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,because my relationship with Jehovah—
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.69,0:05:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it can’t be compared to anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.70,0:05:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything that this world offers is all short-lived,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.62,0:05:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and it’s only an illusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.54,0:05:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,People see only one side of the picture\N—the fame and the money.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.00,0:05:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The other side are\Nthe injuries and disappointments.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.13,0:05:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s very hard psychologically and emotionally;
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.92,0:05:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,you have no freedom.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.55,0:05:25.47,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s why it’s better\Nto give the very best to the One
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.47,0:05:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,who appreciates it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.64,0:05:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,What you do for Jehovah\Nwill always bring you happiness,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.35,0:05:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,joy, and satisfaction.
